    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You could use the searchFunction for that:\n\n``` js\nvar search = instantsearch({\n  searchFunction(helper) {\n    // do something like showing a loading thing\n    // when ready, use\n    helper.search();\n  }\n});\n\ninstantsearch.on('render', function() {\n  // remove the loading indicator\n});\n```\n\nAlthough we do not recommend this, maybe show a very small fake progression bar showing everything is allright to the user if he needs some progress.\n\nIt also depends if those users were used to your old possibly slow search, those may be a bit lost but new users won't notice.\n",
